Q1.What problem does Salesforce solve?
ANS:
Salesforce helps companies manage their customers, sales, services, and business processes in one cloud-based platform.
It solves problems like:
i.Scattered customer data.
ii.Poor communication with customers.
iii.Manual tracking of sales and support.
iv.Difficulty in managing leads and business workflows.
Using Salesforce, businesses can improve customer relationships and increase productivity.

Q2.What is CRM?
ANS:
CRM stands for Customer Relationship Management.
It is a system used to store and manage customer information, interactions, sales, and support activities.
Purpose of CRM:
i.Track customer details
ii.Improve customer service
iii.Manage sales and leads
iv.Build better customer relationships
Example: Salesforce is a popular CRM platform.

Q3.What is an Object in Salesforce? Give one example.
ANS:
An Object in Salesforce is like a database table used to store information.
It contains records and fields.
Example:
Student Object -> stores student details like Name, Roll Number, Course, etc.
Other standard examples:
i.Account
ii.Contact
iii.Opportunity

Q4.Difference between Salesforce Admin and Developer 
ANS:
i.Salesforce Admin
*Manages users, security, reports, and dashboards
Configures Salesforce without much coding
Creates workflows and automations
Maintains and monitors the Salesforce system
Salesforce Developer
Develops custom applications and features
Uses coding languages like Apex and Lightning Web Components (LWC)
Creates integrations with other applications
Builds custom business logic and functionalities
